John Lewis Partnership Plc said
weekly sales at its U.K. department stores increased 1.2 percent
from the year-ago period, driven by demand for toys and
menswear.  Sales were 103.7 million pounds ($163 million) in the
week to Dec. 4, the London-based company said in an e-mailed
statement today. The figure is a 3.7 percent increase on the
previous week.  Weekly sales on the companyâ€™s website rose 47 percent on
